---
import { db, eq, video } from "../lib/db";
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

const allVideos = await db.select().from(video).where(eq(video.publish, 1));
const totalVideos = allVideos.length;
const years = allVideos.map((v) => new Date(v.recorded_at).getUTCFullYear());
const minYear = Math.min(...years);
---

<Layout
  title="About"
  description="The story of If You Make It and the Pink Couch Sessions: a DIY punk video archive started by Dave Garwacke in New Paltz, NY."
>
  <article class="about-page container">
    <header class="about-header">
      <h1>About</h1>
      <p class="about-lede">
        A DIY punk video archive, {totalVideos} videos deep, filmed
        {minYear}–2014, most famously from a pink couch.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>The story</h2>
      <p>
        Dave Garwacke started If You Make It in New Paltz, NY in 2006,
        frustrated that the house shows and performances happening around him
        weren't being documented. He began hauling recording gear to friends'
        shows, and when he moved to Brooklyn the project moved with him,
        couch and all.
      </p>
      <p>
        The Pink Couch Sessions are the heart of it: touring bands passing
        through the tri-state area would stop by Dave's apartment, sit down
        on the pink couch, and play a song or two acoustic. The first session
        went up on September 26, 2007, with Laura Stevenson playing
        &ldquo;Amphibian.&rdquo; The series ran regularly through 2012, with
        archival videos surfacing into 2013, and racked up over a million
        views along the way.
      </p>
      <p>
        The goal was always simple: keep a record of artists Dave admired and
        help get them heard. Alongside the sessions, If You Make It put out
        articles, comics, music videos, and releases on a donation-based
        record label.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>Who played</h2>
      <p>
        Laura Stevenson, Hop Along, Waxahatchee, Tigers Jaw, The Menzingers,
        The Bouncing Souls, Andrew Jackson Jihad, Bomb the Music Industry!,
        Fake Problems, Mikey Erg, Matt Pryor, Mixtapes, RVIVR, The Sidekicks,
        A.W., Direct Hit, Aye Nako, Walter Schreifels, Spraynard, Braid, and
        a couple hundred more. <a href="/artists/">Browse every artist.</a>
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>How it was made</h2>
      <p>
        The early sessions were shot on a Panasonic GS-320 with no external
        mics and no manual gain, just the sound of the room. Later sessions
        upgraded to a Canon HF100 in HD with an AT-822 stereo condenser
        microphone. 
      </p>
    </section>

    <p class="about-source">
      Some of this history is also on
      <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pink_Couch_Sessions" rel="external"
        >Wikipedia ↗</a
      >.
    </p>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .about-page {
    max-width: 46rem;
    padding-block: 2.5rem 3rem;
  }
  .about-header h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  }
  .about-lede {
    font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 2vw, 1.25rem);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .about-section {
    margin-block-start: 2.25rem;
  }
  .about-section h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(1.15rem, 2.5vw, 1.5rem);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    padding-inline-start: 0.6rem;
    border-inline-start: 6px solid var(--color-pink);
  }
  .about-section p {
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    max-width: 62ch;
  }
  .about-section a,
  .about-source a {
    color: var(--color-ink);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: var(--color-pink);
    text-decoration-thickness: 2px;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }
  .about-section a:hover,
  .about-source a:hover {
    color: var(--color-pink-deep);
  }
  .about-source {
    margin-block-start: 2.5rem;
    padding-block-start: 1.25rem;
    border-top: var(--border);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
  }
</style>
